label chapter_1thesignalinthenoiseindexchapter1thesignalinthenoise:
    # ### Chapter 1: The Signal in the Noise \index{Chapter 1: The Signal in the Noise}
    # (blank line)
    ""The alert screams in your neural lace, a shard of ice-cold panic in the warm hum of your consciousness. It’s 03:17. Outside your hab-unit window, the unrelenting early winter La Niña rain streaks down the permaglass, blurring the neon signs of the noodle shops and gene-splicing parlors thirty stories below. You are already awake. You are always already awake.""
    # (blank line)
    ""You don’t move. You don’t have to. You conjure the terminal in your vision, a pane of shimmering, translucent black overlaid on the gray concrete wall of your room. The text is a crisp, calming white. Your fingers twitch, but the commands are already forming in your mind, translated into action by the Gemini-CLI fused to your cortex.""
    # (blank line)
