    ""Your second real date is a trip to the Grand Central Market, a chaotic, vibrant labyrinth of food stalls and crowded walkways in the heart of the lower city. The air is a thick, intoxicating mix of a hundred different spices, sizzling meats, and fresh synth-bread. Zorya is in her element, laughing as she pulls you from a stall selling Martian-grown coffee to one offering genetically engineered fruits that shimmer with an internal light. She is a splash of brilliant color in the drab, utilitarian world you’ve always known.""
