    "... A calling card?\" Kevin let out a short, sharp laugh devoid of humor. \"Danny, that's not a calling card. That's a weapon. A very, very dangerous one. You're not talking about a pretty piece of math. You're talking about a key. A key that can unlock almost any system on the planet. An adaptive prime distribution... that's the holy grail of malware. It learns. It evolves. It's designed to be a ghost in the machine until it decides not to be."
    # (blank line)
    ""He leaned forward across the table, his voice dropping. "Whoever sent you that isn't looking for a new hire. They're making a declaration of war. This is out of your league, Danny. It's out of everyone's league. My advice? Burn the memory of it from your mind and walk away."""
