    ""The conversation shifted back to safer topics, but the warning lingered in the crisp mountain air, a cold counterpoint to the warmth of the pizza oven. Kevin saw the weapon. Alan had seen the beauty. And Daniel... Daniel was having dinner with the bomb.""
    # (blank line)
    ""A few months later, on their next pilgrimage to Boulder, they chose the Gregory Canyon trail, a steeper, more challenging climb that took them deep into the foothills. The air was cooler here, the scent of pine and damp earth more intense. BailieBoy was in his element, his nose to the ground, deciphering the complex tapestry of smells. The strange, alien scent was back, stronger this time. It was a puzzle he couldn’t solve, a scent that was both alluring and unsettling. He followed it for a few yards, his tail low, his body tense with a hunter’s focus. The trail of the scent led him to a small, almost invisible crack in a rock face. The smell was stronger here, a strange mix of warm fur, milk, and the cold, clean scent of ozone. He whined, a low, questioning sound, and pawed at the rock.""
    # (blank line)
    ""“What is it, boy?” Daniel asked, crouching down beside him. “Smell something interesting?”""
