    # #### A Brief Survey of Star-faring Civilizations
    # (blank line)
    ""*   **The Galactic Core:** The heart of the Milky Way is a chaotic, high-energy environment, home to ancient, enigmatic civilizations. Many are in a state of managed decline, their once-great empires having long since turned inward. They are masters of energy and matter manipulation, but have little interest in the affairs of the younger, more volatile civilizations of the spiral arms.""
    # (blank line)
    ""*   **The Norma and Scutum-Centaurus Arms:** These arms are home to a number of aggressive, expansionist species. The Consensus database notes several ongoing, low-level conflicts over resources and territory. These civilizations are generally considered to be technologically advancing, but their focus on military applications has led to a stagnation in other areas of development.""
    # (blank line)
    ""*   **The Perseus Arm:** This arm is a galactic frontier, sparsely populated and largely unexplored. It is here that evidence of truly ancient, vanished civilizations is most often found. Gigantic, silent structures of unknown purpose orbit dead stars, and entire planets have been found carved with geometric patterns that defy natural explanation. These discoveries are a source of endless fascination and debate among the member species of the Consensus, a constant reminder of the galaxy's deep and mysterious history.""
