label fofstechnology:
    # #### FoF's Technology
    ""FoF's civilization, while advanced, adheres to a strict non-aggression principle, which is reflected in their technology. They frown on offensive weaponry, but their defensive capabilities are formidable. At the nano level, her suit and personal environment are protected by a swarm of microscopic drones that provide sophisticated protection against microbes and pathogens. At the macro level, she possesses a powerful personal shield. Its default configuration is a skin-tight field that protects her fur, but it can be expanded in a nanosecond. This shield can be used to directionally push objects away with immense force. On her non-verbal request, it can expand from anywhere within Earth's circumference to push even the most massive human tanks, land vehicles, or even entire aircraft carrier fleets into low Earth polar orbits. Her ship's shields are even more powerful, capable of generating fields that can literally move mountains to other planets. However, even this incredible technology is incomprehensibly primitive compared to the capabilities of the Sentinel.""
    # (blank line)
    ""3i/ATLAS was, to the humans, a mystery. An object that defied easy categorization, its trajectory and behavior unlike any comet or asteroid they had ever observed. To FoF, however, it was a known quantity. It was a probe from a civilization on the fringes of the galactic core, a species known for their clumsy, almost brutish, attempts at interstellar exploration. Their technology was impressive by human standards, but to FoF’s people, it was laughably primitive. The 3i/ATLAS probe was a testament to their lack of subtlety, a loud, clumsy visitor blundering into a system that was already being quietly and meticulously observed.""
