    # (blank line)
    ""FoF’s personal cabin was not a room, but a grove. It was a circular space where the "walls" were a seamless, living tapestry of bioluminescent moss that pulsed with a soft, gentle light, their colors shifting in slow, hypnotic patterns that mirrored her own state of mind. The air was sweet with the scent of night-blooming flowers that grew in spiraling patterns across the floor, their petals unfurling in response to her presence. Her "chair" was a smooth, polished stone that had molded itself to her preferred posture over years of use, warmed from within by the ship's energy.""
