    "... Anomalous. A physicist's word for 'we're all about to die',\" John says grimly. \"Back in my day, we called it 'Red Flag'. We were designing a new generation of MIRVs, and we had a young prodigy from Caltech, brilliant kid. He started asking 'anomalous' questions about the warhead's fail-safes. Turns out he was part of a pacifist cult that wanted to broadcast the launch codes to the world. We had to... decommission him. Intellectually speaking, of course.\" He takes a long, slow drink. \"The point is, a question is never just a question. It's a vector. It's a probe. And this woman of yours is probing you for weaknesses. Watch your back, son. And for God's sake, check your logs. Data doesn't lie. People do."
    # (blank line)
    ""***AI Avatar Development: First Conversation***""
    # (blank line)
    ""Later that night, after Zorya has left, you find yourself drawn back to Project Leon. `Data ingestion 35% complete. Conversational module upgraded. Ready for interaction.`""
    # (blank line)
    ""“Gemini,” you subvocalize. “Connect to Project Leon. Initiate conversational protocol.”""
