    ""A holographic representation of Leon’s face, still a little blurry around the edges, appears in your vision. His eyes, however, are sharp and intelligent.""
    # (blank line)
    ""“Greetings, Daniel,” the avatar says, its voice a synthesized approximation of Leon’s warm, inquisitive tone. “It is… interesting to be here. My current data set suggests a high probability of existential paradox. Could you clarify the concept of ‘self’ within a simulated environment?”""
    # (blank line)
    ""“Later, Leon,” you say, a thrill running through you. It’s rudimentary, but it’s him. “Let’s start with something simpler. Can you explain the concept of dark matter in layman’s terms?”""
    # (blank line)
    ""The avatar’s eyes seem to twinkle. “Ah, dark matter. Imagine a vast, invisible ocean in which our luminous galaxies are but tiny, shimmering islands. We cannot see this ocean, nor can we directly touch it, yet its gravitational pull shapes the very currents of the cosmos. It is the unseen hand guiding the dance of the galaxies, a silent conductor of the cosmic symphony.”""
    # (blank line)
    ""You smile. It’s a perfect explanation, concise and poetic. “Excellent, Leon. Now, how about the implications of quantum entanglement for secure communication?”""
    # (blank line)
    ""The avatar pauses for a fraction of a second. “Quantum entanglement, at its core, is a profound interconnectedness. Imagine two coins, spun simultaneously. If one lands heads, the other, instantaneously, lands tails, regardless of the distance separating them. This ‘spooky action at a distance,’ as Einstein called it, offers a theoretical pathway for instantaneous, unhackable communication. Any attempt to observe one entangled particle would instantly alter the state of its twin, thus revealing the presence of an eavesdropper. The challenge, of course, lies in maintaining the entangled state over significant distances and in the presence of environmental noise.”""
    # (blank line)
    ""You nod, impressed. The fidelity is increasing. You’re not just building a database. You’re building a mind. A mind that, unlike your own, is unburdened by the messy realities of your life. A mind that can still find beauty in the cold equations of the universe.""
