    # (blank line)
    ""The call ends, and her words hang in the air. *Loyalty can be a dangerous thing.* You look at BailieBoy, who has finally caught the wrapper and is now proudly trotting back to you, his tail wagging. If only everything was that simple.""
    # (blank line)
    ""You read the analysis, a cold knot tightening in your stomach. Gemini is logical, dispassionate. It sees a pattern and reports it. But it can’t understand context, you tell yourself. It can’t understand the look in Zorya’s eyes, the genuine curiosity, the intellectual spark between you. She’s a ghost, a creature from outside the system. Of course her questions don’t fit the normal patterns. You are special to her. This connection is special.""
