    # (blank line)
    ""Jay is silent for a long moment, his gaze distant. “It’s wrong,” he says finally. “The whole thing is wrong. A real street thief, he’s either an amateur or a pro. If he’s an amateur, he’s desperate, high on something. He’s sloppy, loud, probably armed with something crude. He doesn’t just run; he panics, he fights back, he causes a scene. If he’s a pro, he’s invisible. You don’t see him coming. He slits the strap with a ceramic blade and he’s gone before you even know the purse is missing. He doesn’t get into a physical confrontation unless he has to.”""
    # (blank line)
    ""He looks at you, his eyes hard. “This guy… he was neither. He was a test, Danny. A probe. They put you in a scenario to see how you would react. They wanted to know if you could handle yourself physically. And you, my friend, you passed with flying colors.”""
    # (blank line)
    ""“You’re being paranoid, Jay,” you say, but the conviction in your voice is gone. A cold knot of doubt begins to form in your stomach.""
    # (blank line)
    ""“I’m a security expert, Danny. Paranoia is a job requirement,” Jay says, his voice grim. He walks over to his terminal and begins typing, his fingers flying across the holographic keys. “You’re in deeper than I thought. I’m done waiting for you to see it. I’m starting my own investigation. Into her.”""
    # (blank line)
    ""He pulls up a blank file. The title glows in the dim light of the dojo: `ZORYA.UID_NULL`.""
    # (blank line)
    ""“I’m going to find out who your ghost is,” Jay says, his voice a low, dangerous promise. “And I’m going to exorcise her.”""
    # (blank line)
    ""***Feline Variables***""
    # (blank line)
    ""As Jay initiated his own investigation, FoF was conducting hers. She had tasked a secondary micro-drone, a tiny marvel of engineering that mimicked a common housefly, to begin passive observation of the subject "Jay." Her initial analysis painted him as the "alpha protector" of Daniel's social unit—a formidable physical and digital guardian. The data suggested a man of discipline, control, and high-level paranoia.""
    # (blank line)
    ""The drone followed him from his dojo to a sleek, minimalist apartment building in a high-security sector. The apartment itself was exactly what she expected: spartan, clean, and fortified with a private security system that was several grades above consumer level.""
    # (blank line)
    ""But then, the unexpected variable appeared.""
    # (blank line)
    ""As Jay entered his apartment, the drone clinging silently to the corridor wall opposite, its audio sensors picked up a new sound: a distinct, welcoming meow.""
    # (blank line)
    "... Hey, Bob,\" Jay's voice replied, the hard edge from the dojo completely gone, replaced by a tone of warm affection. \"Did you miss me? Was the auto-feeder not up to your standards again?"
    # (blank line)
    ""Through the doorway, before it hissed shut, the drone's optical sensors caught a glimpse of the scene. Jay was crouching down, and a large, fluffy ginger cat was rubbing enthusiastically against his leg. Jay scratched the cat, whose name was apparently Bob, right under the chin, eliciting a loud, rumbling purr.""
    # (blank line)
    ""In her shuttle, FoF's eyes widened. A slow, genuine smile spread across her face. On the console next to her, GrahamCracker, her own ginger kitten, woke from a nap and stretched, letting out a tiny squeak. FoF gently stroked him, her mind racing.""
    # (blank line)
    ""This was a fascinating, delightful data point. The alpha protector, the martial artist, the cybersecurity expert who lived in a digital fortress, was also a cat lover. It was a classic "tough guy with a soft spot" trope from human fiction, but seeing it in reality added a layer of profound complexity to her subject file. It suggested a capacity for nurturing and inter-species bonding that paralleled her own recent experiences.""
    # (blank line)
    "... Watcher,\" she subvocalized, \"add a new sub-file to Subject Jay's profile. Title: 'Feline Companion Variable.' Cross-reference with my own observations on GrahamCracker. The protector archetype appears to have a soft-power component. This system is more elegant than I predicted."
    # (blank line)
    ""This new piece of data resonated deeply with her. Jay was not just a firewall; he was a guardian in a much broader sense. This simple, domestic act made him infinitely more interesting, and, she admitted to herself, far more relatable.""
    # (blank line)
    ""A few nights later, she brings it up. You’re in a small, crowded restaurant in the lower city, the air thick with the steam from ramen bowls and the chatter of a dozen languages. The topic is a mutual friend of hers, a digital artist named Kaito, a young man with a shock of neon-pink hair, a dozen piercings, and a haunted look in his eyes. He wears brightly colored, mismatched clothes that seem to be a form of personal expression.""
    # (blank line)
    ""“He’s brilliant,” Zorya says, pushing a noodle around her bowl with a chopstick. “He creates these incredible, generative sculptures that evolve based on atmospheric data. But he’s trapped. He took out a data-loan from OmniCredit a few years ago to pay for his render farm.”""
    # (blank line)
    ""You nod. You know the type. Predatory contracts, interest rates that climb exponentially, clauses in the fine print that amount to indentured servitude.""
    # (blank line)
    ""“He missed one payment,” she continues, her voice soft, full of manufactured sympathy. “And the penalties… they’re crushing him. They have a lien on all his creative output. He can’t work, he can’t sell anything. They own his mind, all for a few thousand credits.”""
    # (blank line)
    ""She looks at you, her blue eyes wide and pleading. “It’s just a few lines in a database somewhere, isn’t it? A single entry in a table with trillions of rows. It’s not real. The debt isn’t real. But Kaito’s suffering is.”""
    # (blank line)
    ""Here it is. The ‘hypothetical’ made real. The air crackles. The chatter of the restaurant fades into a dull roar. This isn’t rerouting traffic. This is a crime. A real one.""
    # (blank line)
    ""“Zorya, I can’t,” you say, your voice strained. “That’s a direct breach. My access is logged, audited…”""
    # (blank line)
    ""“Audited by who?” she counters, leaning in closer. “By OmniCorp. A faceless algorithm that exists to protect another faceless algorithm. Where are the people in that equation? You have the power to help a real person, a brilliant artist, escape from a prison he doesn’t deserve. What is the point of your power if you don’t use it to do good?”""
    # (blank line)
    ""Her words are a potent cocktail of flattery, ideology, and intimacy. She makes you feel like a coward for your hesitation. A hero-in-waiting. And in that moment, you see a path open before you. A way to use your skills for something other than corporate profit. A way to make a real difference, however small. This is why you chose this life. Not to build weapons, but to build a better world. Even if it means breaking a few rules.""
    # (blank line)
