    # (blank line)
    ""The call ends, and you’re left with a profound sense of guilt. Karin’s trust in you is a heavy weight, a stark reminder of the world you’re about to betray. She sees you as a good man, a brilliant engineer, a valued member of her team. And you’re about to become a criminal.""
    # (blank line)
    ""The next day, you walk BailieBoy through the manicured lawns of the park adjacent to the OmniCorp Library. The sky is a uniform grey, the air thick with the smell of rain. Children are playing on the holographic jungle gym, their laughter echoing in the damp air. You watch them, a knot of anxiety tightening in your stomach. Zorya’s request is a virus in your system, a piece of malware that is slowly corrupting your core programming. You’ve spent your life building and maintaining systems, living by the rules of a world that is anything but fair. Now, you’re being asked to break those rules, to become a ghost in the machine for a cause that feels both righteous and terrifyingly dangerous.""
    # (blank line)
    ""You wrestle with it for a full minute, the silence stretching between you. Gemini is silent in your head, awaiting a command, offering no judgment. It has already given its warning. The choice is yours. You look at Zorya’s hopeful, beautiful face. You think of the faceless, predatory corporation. You make a decision.""
    # (blank line)
